

--- Kernel and /proc

- ls /proc

- SSH
#ps auxw | egrep sshd
#ls -l /proc/1130


- SYSTEM INFO

/proc/cpuinfo
/proc/meminfo
/proc/mounts
/proc/cmdline


- Network info
# ls /sys/class/net/
ens160  ens256  lo
# cat /sys/class/net/ens256/operstate 
up



- kernel I/O schedulers
# cat /sys/block/sda/queue/scheduler 
none [mq-deadline] kyber bfq 

- changed files

atime -- access time = last time file opened

mtime -- modified time = last time file contents was modified

ctime -- changed time = last time file inode was modified

Numeric arguments can be specified as

+n     for greater than n,
-n     for less than n,
n      for exactly n.

# find /etc -type f -mtime -1
/etc/fstab


